    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-16T10:10:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-16T10:10:00-05:00" n="548"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d548">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">800.42/11–2844: Airgram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-16T11:10:00-04:00"
                            >December 16, 1944—11:10 a.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>A–2676. Reference Embassy’s Airgram 1419, November 28. Department now reviewing
                    earlier plans for United Nations organization in educational and cultural field
                    in view of changes in general situation since last April and the clarification
                    of the framework of international organization developed by the Dumbarton Oaks
                    Conference.</p>
                <p>Kefauver will return to London with instructions for participation in informal
                    discussions with representatives of the British government concerning United
                    Nations educational and cultural organization. Suggest proposed exchange of
                    views be delayed until his arrival in January or soon thereafter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
